[Auction "W"]
2C pass 3D pass 3NT pass 6NT pass pass pass
[Result ""]
{WEST has a balanced hand with 23 points. He opens 2♣ and expects to rebid 2NT.

EAST has 12 points so makes a positive response in her best suit. Since that suit is

♦

s she must jump to the 3-level.

WEST now describes his balanced, minimum hand by bidding 3NT.

EAST bids 6NT, knowing that the partnership holds at least 34 points.}
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 4, chOption: W, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:3, nBasis: 2, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]

